  $ kurv_

  Tool to sign files using EdDSA (Ed25519 + Blake2b)
  Example workflow:

    1. generate a keypair:
       this generates two files, <base>.pub and <base>.priv,
       you can publish <base>.pub, but <base>.priv has to
       be secret.

       $ kurv -g id
       $ ls
       file.txt id.pub id.priv

    2. sign a file:

       $ kurv -sP id.priv file.txt > file-signed.txt

    3. check signature:
       if a public key file is not specified, then kurv
       searches for public keys in $KURV_KEYRING.

       $ kurv -cp id.pub file-signed.txt > file-signed.txt
       $ KURV_KEYRING='...' kurv -c file-signed.txt


    4. detach signature:
       remove a signature from a file:

       $ kurv -d file-signed.txt

